==============================================================================
Third-party components and their licenses
==============================================================================

This product bundles or depends on the following third-party software.
The list documents what is shipped inside the NeuroBoot source tree,
inside the generated ISO, or downloaded by users while following the
build instructions (docs/BUILD.md).

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. Noto Sans SC font
   - Path in repo: app/assets/fonts/NotoSansSC-Regular.ttf (~2.4 MB)
   - Bundled in:   neuroboot.exe via include_bytes! macro
   - License:      SIL Open Font License, Version 1.1
   - Upstream:     https://fonts.google.com/noto/specimen/Noto+Sans+SC

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2. Microsoft Visual C++ Runtime DLLs (CRT redist)
   - Path in repo: pe-build/payload/crt-redist/ (17 DLLs, ~1.9 MB)
                   - vcruntime140.dll
                   - ucrtbase.dll
                   - api-ms-win-crt-*.dll (15 UCRT umbrella DLLs)
   - Distributed under Microsoft's "Distributable Code" terms for the
     Visual Studio Subscription. These DLLs are required for llama-server.exe
     (a non-static msvc build) to start inside Windows PE, which does
     not bundle the Visual C++ Runtime by default.
   - Source: Visual Studio 2026 VC redist (vcruntime140) +
             Windows 10 SDK 10.0.26100.0 Redist (api-ms-win-crt-*) +
             C:\Windows\System32 (ucrtbase)
   - Reproduce with: tools-dev/collect-crt-redist.ps1

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3. llama.cpp (runtime binary, NOT bundled in this repo)
   - Used by:     NeuroBoot to run local GGUF model inference (llama-server.exe)
   - Distributed: Inside the generated NeuroBoot.iso under \NeuroBoot\llama-cpp\
                  (downloaded separately per docs/BUILD.md section 1.4)
   - License:     MIT License
   - Upstream:    https://github.com/ggml-org/llama.cpp

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4. Mesa3D (llvmpipe software OpenGL renderer)
   - Used by:     NeuroBoot for OpenGL rendering inside Windows PE (no GPU drivers)
   - Distributed: Inside the generated NeuroBoot.iso as opengl32.dll +
                  libgallium_wgl.dll next to neuroboot.exe
                  (downloaded as mesa-dist-win release per docs/BUILD.md)
   - License:     MIT License (Mesa core); see Mesa's own license terms for
                  detailed per-component licenses.
   - Upstream:    https://www.mesa3d.org/  /  https://github.com/pal1000/mesa-dist-win

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
5. Qwen3-4B-Instruct-2507 (GGUF quantized weights)
   - Used by:     llama-server.exe for local AI inference (default model)
   - Distributed: Inside the generated NeuroBoot.iso (~2.33 GB)
                  (downloaded separately per docs/BUILD.md section 1.5)
   - License:     Apache License 2.0 (Qwen series license)
   - Upstream:    https://huggingface.co/Qwen/Qwen3-4B-Instruct-2507

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6. Ventoy (recommended user-side multi-boot USB tool)
   - Role:        Recommended way to install NeuroBoot.iso to a USB stick.
                  Not bundled in this repo; user downloads separately per
                  docs/BUILD.md.
   - License:     GNU General Public License, Version 3
   - Upstream:    https://www.ventoy.net/

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
7. Microsoft Windows ADK / WinPE add-on (build-time dependency)
   - Role:        Provides copype, DISM, oscdimg, and the WinPE base image
                  (boot.wim) that NeuroBoot.iso is built on top of.
   - License:     Microsoft EULA. Build-time only; not redistributed by
                  this repo. The generated NeuroBoot.iso contains a customized
                  WinPE image and is subject to the WinPE redistribution terms
                  documented by Microsoft.
   - Upstream:    https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows-hardware/get-started/adk-install

==============================================================================
Rust crate dependencies
==============================================================================

The Rust source tree (app/) depends on a number of open-source crates from
crates.io. The complete dependency tree with versions is recorded in
app/Cargo.lock. Run `cargo tree` for a full listing or `cargo license` (after
installing the cargo-license subcommand) for a license summary. Notable direct
dependencies and their licenses:

   eframe      (egui application framework)     ........ MIT OR Apache-2.0
   egui                                          ........ MIT OR Apache-2.0
   reqwest     (HTTP client, rustls TLS)         ........ MIT OR Apache-2.0
   serde, serde_json                             ........ MIT OR Apache-2.0
   rfd         (file dialog, Win32 backend)      ........ MIT
   base64                                        ........ MIT OR Apache-2.0

